<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1084,1252]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Taxonomic notes. Described originally as a species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Protoplanes" authorityName="Protoplanes" box="[805,1111,1119,1144]" class="Chilopoda" family="Linotaeniidae" genus="Scolioplanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[805,948,1120,1144]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Scolioplanes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[964,1100,1120,1144]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Protoplanes</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
, it was assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[1326,1435,1120,1143]" class="Chilopoda" family="Linotaeniidae" genus="Strigamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1326,1435,1120,1143]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Strigamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dobroruka" box="[187,393,1156,1180]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Dobroruka, L. J. (1977) Chilopoden aus Griechenland und Kreta in der Sammlung des Nationalmuseums Prag. V e stnik C eskoslovenske Spole c nosti zoologicke, 41, 161 - 164." type="journal article" year="1977">
Dobroruka (
<number box="[325,385,1156,1180]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1977.0">1977</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, though misspelled as “ 
<taxonomicName box="[665,895,1157,1180]" class="Chilopoda" family="Linotaeniidae" genus="Strigamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis box="[665,895,1157,1180]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Strigamia caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. It was almost ignored in the literature, but its validity was never questioned.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
